+- Index schema version 38 makes derived freshness exact for contentless message
+  FTS and provider-usage insights. `messages_fts_identity` shadows each indexed
+  rowid with block identity, source content hash, FTS recipe, and output
+  contract; all trigger and repair routes maintain it atomically, and readiness
+  rejects missing, excess, rowid-reused, source-mismatched, or recipe-mismatched
+  rows even when counts are equal. `insight_materialization` gains typed
+  source/recipe/output receipts, monotonic generation, and explicit
+  pending/current/degraded state. Provider-usage source triggers mark an
+  existing receipt pending on event or message-token mutation, while rebuild
+  stamps the exact durable input identity and active pricing-catalog recipe.
+  Existing index tiers must be rebuilt from source evidence
+  (`polylogue ops reset --index && polylogued run`); derived tiers have no
+  in-place migration chain.
+- Embeddings schema version 3 adds per-session desired/materialized derivation
+  keys and attempt receipts. The key binds exact embeddable message content,
+  model/dimension and the full computational recipe, while generation and
+  attempt identity prevent superseded workers from publishing vectors or
+  clearing newer debt. A complete session replacement promotes vectors, status,
+  metadata, and the receipt in one SQLite transaction. Existing embeddings
+  tiers must be rebuilt or blue-green replaced; there is no in-place derived
+  migration.
